8fcb			; https://tutorials.eeems.ca/ASMin28Days/lesson/day16.html#cmp 
8fcb			 
8fcb			; String Length 
8fcb			;With a length-prefixed string, finding the length is trivial. For a null-terminated string, the process is decidedly more involved. This is where CPIR comes in. 
8fcb			 
8fcb			; Get the length of the null-terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8fcb			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8fcb			 
8fcb			strlenz: 
8fcb			 
8fcb af			    XOR    A               ; Zero is the value we are looking for. 
8fcc 47			    LD     B, A             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8fcd 4f			    LD     C, A             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8fce			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8fce ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8fd0			 
8fd0			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8fd0 67			    LD     H, A             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8fd1 6f			    LD     L, A             ; number of bytes 
8fd2 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8fd4 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8fd5 c9				ret 
8fd6			 
8fd6			; Get the length of the A terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8fd6			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8fd6			 
8fd6			strlent: 
8fd6			 
8fd6			                  ; A is the value we are looking for. 
8fd6 06 00		    LD     B, 0             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8fd8 0e 00		    LD     C, 0             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8fda			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8fda ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8fdc			 
8fdc			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8fdc 26 00		    LD     H, 0             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8fde 2e 00		    LD     L, 0             ; number of bytes 
8fe0 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8fe2 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8fe3 c9				ret 
